Description: Eye Of Gnome image viewer
DescDetail: <<
This is the Eye of Gnome, an image viewer program.  It is meant to be
a fast and functional image viewer as well as an image cataloging
program.
<<
DescPort: <<
	Added librsvg2-gtk as Depends to be able to open svg files

	Fix some pygobject symbol mess. Patch from comment #1 of:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=506421

	Make sure local -I come first. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=560070

	Link against local libs directly instead of -L/-l. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=560073

	Avoid collision of local variable with wait.h symbol. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=560065

	Uh oh, crc32_combine but it's marked private in 10.4's libz
	(fixed in 10.5). Keep at older %v that doesn't need it. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=560068
<<
DescPackaging: <<
	Disable xmp because we don't have its support available

	Disable python bindings. If someone wants them, would roll a
	separate -pyXX package set.
<<
